description:
&lt;p&gt;As part of the Innovation &amp; Intelligent Automation team, we are recruiting a talented team to scale and accelerate the deployment of automation in the Trust and wider health and care community.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have the opportunity to work with highly complex automation projects and will be part of a team creating world-class automation solutions across clinical and corporate areas regionally and nationally.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role of Robotics Operational Support is pivotal to our success and vision, we are looking for a driven individual, who is excited by daily challenges and thrive in a busy and ever-changing environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an individual who can support embedded Digital within the wider clinical and corporate teams to ensure its widespread transformation benefit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This person will be responsible for the operational support of the Trust’s Robotic Process Automation environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Through the use of cloud-based automation tools and software, the Intelligent Automation team assist the Trust in the delivery of cost-effective, risk-controlled, robust, reliable, responsive and secure automation solutions to assist the organisation in eliminating paper and improving efficiency, the post holder will be key to supporting this work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;One of the primary functions is to operationally support the automation platform but will also participate in all areas of the robotic automation development lifecycle including design, programming, versioning control, testing, documentation, technical implementation and deployment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Finally, you will bring a high level of expertise, and a passion for supporting the goals and ambitions of the team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
